Olympus Optical Co Ltd &lt;OOPT.T> predictedparent company current profit of 5.50 billion yen in the yearending October 31, 1987, up 12 pct from a year earlier,assuming a yen/dollar rate of 147 yen in the second half, acompany spokesman told Reuters.    Sales in 1986/87 are estimated at 122 billion yen, up 0.9pct from a year earlier.    But net profit will fall 71.7 pct to three billion yen in1986/87 from a year earlier when the company made a 10.59billion net profit due to sales of real estate assets worthseven billion yen, the spokesman said.    The precision instrument maker will retain 13 yen dividendfor 1986/87, the spokesman said.    It earlier reported parent company net profit of 1.34billion yen in the six months ended April 30, down 85.5 pctfrom a year earlier, on sales of 60.92 billion, down 0.1 pct.    The poor net was mainly due to a fall to 45 mln yen inextraordinary profit in the first half, against 7.70 billion ofsuch profit a year earlier, due mainly to sales of assets.    The drop in first half sales was due to the yen's riseagainst the dollar, which cut sales by some 4.30 billion yen.    The dollar averaged 157 yen, against 192 a year earlier. REUTER&#3;